for certain: THE BIG ICELANDIC BANKING CRASH.

In less than a day all the banks crashed because the interest of the foreign borrowing banks was much higher (130% and more) than the money deposited by the Icelandic people where you got a good interest back 4-5%

So when on 8 October 2008 all the 3 biggest Icelandic banks went bankrupt (around 576 billions US$ devaluation) there was allmost a total panic on Iceland and the banking stock- and currency markets went down like you never saw something like it before.

Very low interest rates everywhere

Now the central bank governor exercised his responsibility for the devaluation of the currency by introducing very low interest rates everywhere ( practically for free), all the banks which survived invest in our stock- and currencymarkets.
